# COBOL Parsing Constraints

- Keep targeted COBOL dialect assumptions explicit in code and docs.
- Do not silently drop unsupported constructs; classify and report them.
- Preserve source span mappings through parse, normalize, and transform stages.
- Maintain recoverable error paths to allow partial analysis outputs.
- Track parse coverage metrics by module and codebase snapshot.

## Implementation Guardrails

- Parser changes must include fixtures for dialect edge cases.
- Copybook resolution logic must emit provenance for expanded fields.
- Unknown tokens/nodes must be surfaced in diagnostics and telemetry.
